Posted on September 4, 2008USW, Supporters to Demonstrate at Wayzata Investment Partners Headquarters 

Marketwatch.com, a division of the Wall Street Journal, is carrying a story that indicates that United Steel Workers will be Marching on the headquarters of Wayzata Investment Partners on Friday, September 5th, at 12 noon.
According to the article, ‚ÄúIn June of this year, Wayzata Investment Partners bought the former Pope & Talbot paper mill in Halsey, Ore., and renamed it Cascade Pacific Pulp. In the change of ownership, longtime workers were fired and then made to reapply for their jobs. Wages were slashed from 12 to 28% and employees forced to pay up to $3,000 for deductibles and up to $10,000 in out-of-pocket expenses to retain family health insurance. ‚Äú
The article went on to say, ‚ÄúUSW members from the Oregon plant will be joined by union supporters and community allies from Minnesota at the march and demonstration at Wayzata Investment Partners. This event takes place Friday, Sept. 5, 12 Noon at the firm‚Äôs offices at 701 Lake St, E., Wayzata, Minn. The union delegation will seek a meeting with Wayzata boss Patrick Halloran and urge him to halt the company‚Äôs unfair demands on workers and their community.
Paper mill workers feel this demonstration at the equity firm‚Äôs offices is justified. ‚ÄúIf we have no other way of making contact with absentee owners like Wayzata Investment Partners, we have to go to them,‚Äù said Jim Gourley, financial secretary for USW Local 1189 in Halsey. ‚Äú
Lieutenant Murphy of the Wayzata Police Department had no comment.  I can‚Äôt remember the last time a protest march occurred in Wayzata. Stay tuned to Wayzata.com for the latest breaking news on the protest in front of Wayzata Investment Partners.
